  "name": "Bollinger Bands Volatility Breakout",
  "description": "This strategy utilizes Bollinger Bands to identify trading opportunities during periods of sudden volatility and range contraction. A long position is initiated when the Bollinger Bands Width reaches a 30-day low and the price closes above the upper band, while a short position is taken when the price closes below the lower band under similar conditions.",
  "algorithm_type": "TechnicalPattern",
  "prompt": "Design a technical pattern strategy that trades based on sudden volatility and range contraction. Enter a long position when the 14-period Bollinger Bands Width is at a 30-day low (lowest in 30 periods), and the close breaks above the upper Bollinger Band. Enter a short position when Bollinger Bands Width is at a 30-day low, and the close breaks below the lower Bollinger Band. Exit the trade when price closes back inside the bands or when a 10% expansion from the entry period's Bands Width is registered. Use daily candle data.",
